H0.text: Melting ice is not an example of a chemical change.

H1.text: Corroding silver is not an example of a chemical change.

H2.text: Burning match is NOT an example of a chemical change.

H3.text: Rotting vegetation is not an example of a chemical change.

A4.text: Chemical reactions yield one or more products, which usually have properties different from the reactants.

A5.text: Combustion reaction, an element or compound reacts with an oxidant, usually oxygen.

A6.text: Physical changes occur when objects or substances undergo a change that does not change their chemical composition.

A7.text: Heating and cooling many elements and some compounds change from solids to liquids and from liquids to gases when heated and the reverse when cooled.
